OL,3,C'There are others like us': Government
OL,4,Cconsiders changing Mental Capacity Act
OL,6,FFiona was repeatedly dismissed for
OL,7,Fyears when she tried to get her son a
OL,8,Fmental capacity assessment, which
OL,9,Festablishes whether someone has the
OL,10,Fability to make decisions about their
OL,11,Fown safety and wellbeing, and helps
OL,12,Fdetermine what support they may need.
OL,14,F"The law as it stands didn't enable me
OL,15,Fto save my son's life, even though I'd
OL,16,Fbeen asking for a proper mental
OL,17,Fcapacity assessment. There was no
OL,18,Fmechanism for me to do that," Fiona
OL,19,Fsaid ahead of the meeting.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/21
