OL,3,C'There are others like us': Government
OL,4,Cconsiders changing Mental Capacity Act
OL,6,FIt states that as a starting point
OL,7,Feveryone should be presumed to have
OL,8,Fthe capacity to make their own
OL,9,Fdecisions about their own safety and
OL,10,Fwellbeing, and that assessment should
OL,11,Fbe carried out if their capacity is in
OL,12,Fdoubt.
OL,14,FHowever, research has found that such
OL,15,Fassessments are either not carried out
OL,16,Fenough or are not carried out
OL,17,Feffectively in particular on autistic
OL,18,Fpeople, adults with learning
OL,19,Fdisabilities or those with mental
OL,20,Fhealth issues, such as bipolar and
OL,21,Fschizophrenia.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/21
