OL,3,C'There are others like us': Government
OL,4,Cconsiders changing Mental Capacity Act
OL,6,FThey, along with the National Autistic
OL,7,FSociety, agree the current system is
OL,8,Ffailing autistic adults like
OL,9,FChristopher, as well as other adults
OL,10,Fwith learning disabilities and mental
OL,11,Fhealth illnesses - at times with
OL,12,Fcatastrophic consequences.
OL,14,FThey are concerned there are
OL,15,Fpotentially hundreds of preventable
OL,16,Fdeaths per year due to this issue,
OL,17,Fwith recent research finding The
OL,18,FMental Capacity Act was not followed
OL,19,Fin a quarter of the deaths of autistic
OL,20,Fpeople and those with learning
OL,21,Fdisabilities in 2022 alone.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/21
