OL,3,C'There are others like us': Government
OL,4,Cconsiders changing Mental Capacity Act
OL,6,F"All of these issues start to come to
OL,7,Fthe fore. And one of the key issues in
OL,8,Fthem is whether or not that person has
OL,9,Fthe mental capacity to make a variety
OL,10,Fof different decisions for themselves
OL,11,Fin their life."
OL,13,F'I believed he would die'
OL,15,FOne mother told ITV News that her
OL,16,Fautistic son has been sectioned after
OL,17,Fdeteriorating for years because the
OL,18,Fauthorities judged that he had
OL,19,Fcapacity to decide that he didn't need
OL,20,Fany support.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/21
