OL,3,C'There are others like us': Government
OL,4,Cconsiders changing Mental Capacity Act
OL,6,FAsked how she felt when she heard
OL,7,FFiona's story, Parveen said: "I just
OL,8,Fcried uncontrollably because every
OL,9,Fquote I read, it was almost like I was
OL,10,Ftelling our story. Those very same
OL,11,Fthings about being dismissed as an
OL,12,Fover fussy parent - stop interfering,
OL,13,Fhe's an adult, he can make his own
OL,14,Fdecisions.
OL,16,F"People would come in and see him in
OL,17,Fthis completely sick state - lying in
OL,18,Fhis bed withering away into this tiny
OL,19,Fform - but they wouldn't do anything."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/21
